comments.body:
@xtqqczze This sounds like an issue in visual studio not realizing it needs to restore.  I'm not sure what to tell you.  You or someone else could add a `-RestoreAll` switch to `start-psbuild`.

The `sln` is only there as a connivence.  We make no guarantees for it working to actually build.

@iSazonov has been doing good working getting rid of the workarounds we use in `start-psbuild`, but the team at Microsoft, we don't have an immediate goal to build using Visual Studio.  There is still one workaround, `TypeGen` which I haven't seen him attempt to eliminate.  

As far as why we don't restore everything, we know we can't cross compile, so we limit what we have dotnet restore to save time and disk.

> TypeGen which I haven't seen him attempt to eliminate.

@TravisEz13 I did the attempt years ago but MSFT team said "Oh, no..." :-) If I remember right the team wanted to avoid complex csproj files and prefer PowerShell script. But the TypeGen (like resgen) is stable and we could move it to csproj that helps to build on VS 2019.

If you want I could try to move TypeGen to csproj (It will work like resgen works now)
